:: To check CPU Usuage and running processes ::

To check CPU usage: 
top
Press 1 to check the per core usage at top

To install package: 
sudo dnf install htop -y

To list all the process: 
htop

For 1 process: 
top -p (process-id)

For a specific process with more details:
ps -p (process-id) -o pid,ppid,user,%cpu,%mem,cmd

To install package:
sudo dnf install strace -y

Trace What a Process is Doing:
strace -p 3140184

To list total number of CPU's:
nproc

To list all the CPU's:
lscpu

To install systage package: 
sudo dnf install -y sysstat

Per Core CPU usage:
mpstat -P ALL 1
